{
  "stem": "27507.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we all squeezed into that car with difficulty, because we squeezed-- there were all together nine people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents and I and my father's sister with her husband and child, my cousin, and another-- and a brother of my father, again with wife and child.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So all together, nine people, which was probably quite difficult and stinks as well.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we left Warsaw and started driving east.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The brother of my father was an excellent driver, so we went on, although the-- it was impossible to drive at any speed, because the roads were totally clogged with traffic, with pedestrians, with horse carts, with cars, with lorries.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was all the kind of a picture like one could see later on in films and so on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And moreover, we were all the time strafed and attacked by plane.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were German planes who were attacking and shooting at on the road.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were extremely lucky to have survived that anyway.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it took days.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were-- we were going for days and days.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't remember when we were sleeping there on that occasion.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But after about three or four days, we arrived in Brzesc nad Bugiem.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We crossed the River Bug.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we went further east in Volenia and finally there was-- the petrol that we had was completely finished.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we then-- on one occasion, my father and his brother, I think, went to a village and hired horses, which would pull the car for another 20 or so kilometers to the nearest town.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then they-- and then they managed to get some small amount of petrol, with which we finally got after some eight or nine days to Rowne, which is where a cousin of my brother-- of my father lived.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
